content.htmlText: The neighborhood is very safe and kid & pet friendly. You will see many people out walking their dogs and socializing with each other. The streets are tree lined with gorgeous Jacarandas, simply stunning in the spring time. We are walking distance to everything...shopping and dining. The studios are about a mile away and Rancho Park for golf, tennis and swimming. Beverly Hills is about 5 minutes, Century City 2 minutes and UCLA is about eight minutes, all by car. We are one mile from the 405 fwy and the 10 fwy. Trader Joe's, Ralphs, Sprouts and Wholefoods are close by as well.

The neighborhood is very safe and kid & pet friendly. You will see many people out walking their dogs and socializing with each other. The streets are tree lined with gorgeous Jacarandas, simply stunning in the springtime. We are walking distance to everything...shopping, dining and movies (the mall is one block away). The studios are about a mile away and Rancho Park for golf, tennis and swimming. Beverly Hills is about 5 minutes, Century City 2 minutes and UCLA is about eight minutes, all by car. We are one mile from the 405 fwy and the 10 fwy. Trader Joe's, Ralphs, Sprouts and Whole Foods are close by as well.

If you have a car during your stay, I recommend the "waze" app for your smart phone. It is the best app I have seen for keeping you out of traffic and getting you to your destination in the shortest amount of time.

Public transportation is a 10 minute walk away. This can easily take you anywhere you want to go in the city, Downtown LA, Santa Monica, Beverly Hills or Hollywood etc.

The Metro is a few blocks away and can get you to almost any location in the city.

Uber is a great alternative for those visiting without a car. They are very prompt in picking you up and very reasonable in their fees. Just download the app on your phone, add your payment method, and that's it! You are all set. Your credit card will be charged automatically after you reach your destination.

Some great advice for traveling times in Los Angeles during the week. Plan your trips in the morning going East and North, plan your afternoons going West and South. The traffic can be brutal at times and this will save you a lot of time and aggravation.

section.houseRulesSubtitle: You'll be staying in someone's home, so please treat it with care and respect.

html.htmlText:
Age requirement: Must be 25 years old for person making the booking.
You must read & approve of these house rules before you will be accepted.
If you can not be here by 3:00pm check in, please let me know as soon as possible the time you are expecting to arrive. 
You can not access the property without someone here to let you in.
Please send me a text letting me know if your flight is delayed or if you will be late. If it is after 10PM you may need to arrive the next day.
If you do not have a clear picture of yourself on your profile I will ask to see your photo ID or passport which must match the name on the reservation.
I do not allow other people here in the house, only the guests on the reservation
Please keep to the stair railing while going up or down the stairs
Do not put any wheeled luggage on any of the furniture
Please be mindful of lights and water usage. 
Please do not slam doors. 
Please respect the furnishings. 
Please do not put drinks on the furniture with out protection of a coaster.
Please keep all wet towels in the bathroom.
If you have any issues or need anything in your guest suite please let me know as soon as you can.
If you break or damage something please let me know.
This is a non smoking property. 
No loud music, no drugs or excessive alcohol consumption. 
Please be considerate of my neighbors.
Please behave respectful and responsible during your stay. 
Please do not put wet or damp towels on any of the furniture. 
When using the jacuzzi tub make sure the tub in full of water with no bubble bath or liquid soap before turning on the jets, just hot water.
Use of the washer & dryer for one load of laundry during your stay, hours from 9am -9pm, I will need to be here to show you how to use them  
Please no heavy perfume or men's cologne. 
When you leave please leave the house key, remote and parking permit on my desk near the front door.
Street parking is my Permit only which I will lend to you during your stay. If you don't return it you will be charged $100.00.
If you loose my house key and remote you will be charged $200.00.
Make sure you read the parking signs if you have a car, Thursday and Friday are street cleaning days. Park across the street on Wednesday evening, park in front of the house on Thursday evening.
Please only park on the right side of the street and never park backwards. 
Thank you.

htmlDescription.htmlText:
Enjoy our comfortable and spacious guest bedroom with your own private bathroom! It is centrally located on a quiet street, just blocks away from restaurants and shops. The Metro Line is a few blocks away. The Star Line bus pick up spot is less than a block away. *If you plan on going to more than 5 attractions, try the GO CARD, you can visit up to 34 attractions for one low price. If you want to attend a live show, it’s free!…try www.1iota.com and book your tickets in advance.😁

The space
We are in the heart of the city but while you are inside you feel like you are in the country. It is very quiet and peaceful. Your room is totally private, quiet, clean and spacious with a full size bed and luxurious bed linens. Your private bath has a jacuzzi tub and full shower. Roku TV and wi-fi are included. There is also a hair dryer, soap, shampoo and an iron. To make your stay a little more enjoyable, we added a small refrigerator and a coffee maker.

The property is completely private, you will need a remote to get in and out which we will provide for you.

Street parking is by permit only which I will lend you a parking permit during your stay. You must return it or you will be charged 100.00.

Check in time is 3:00 pm
Check out time is 11:00 am

If you need other arrangement times please let us know and we will try to work with you.

Guest access
Our home is completely private and secure, you will need a remote control and a house key to get in and out which we will provide for you.

STREET PARKING is by permit only which we will provide to you. If you happen to be here on a THURSDAY or FRIDAY please read the signs for the street cleaning times to make sure you are parked on the right side of the street.

Check in time is 3:00 pm
Check out time is 11:00 am

If you need other arrangement times please let us know and we will try to work with you.

If you are not here within and hour of the check in time you will need to make an appointment for when you will arrive so that someone is here to let you in.

We don't mind accommodating you, we just ask that you respect our time and let us know a more accurate time of arrival. Thank you for understanding.

During your stay
We are happy to spend some time with you and to acquaint you with the neighborhood and share all the wonderful things to do and see here in Los Angeles. If you prefer to be alone that is okay too! What ever works for you. We do enjoy meeting new friends and sharing our travel experiences and hope you do too.

Other things to note
We would be happy to help you in any way we can...Just ask. Our home is occupied my husband and myself. We do have two Golden Retrievers and a cat, so if you are allergic please let us know. They are super friendly and will make you feel like family.

License number
HSR19-004993
